info.description: API for movie theater ticketing and services
info.title: AMC Theatres

summary: The AMC Theatres API facilitates movie theater ticketing and related services. It provides endpoints for accessing information about movies, making reservations, checking showtimes, and exploring theatre locations. The API is structured to support various aspects of theater operations, enhancing the movie-going experience for users.

The Amazon API is designed for an e-commerce platform, providing essential endpoints to facilitate online shopping functionalities. Key features include accessing and managing products through `/api/v1/products`, handling shopping cart operations via `/api/v1/cart`, and processing orders with `/api/v1/orders`. This API supports seamless integration for building robust e-commerce solutions.

info.description: API for home services and contractor connections
info.title: Angi

summary: The Angi API is designed to connect users with home services and contractors. It includes endpoints for accessing various functionalities: `/api/v1/providers` for retrieving information on service providers, `/api/v1/reviews` for managing user reviews, `/api/v1/services` for exploring offered services, and `/api/v1/projects` for handling project details. The API facilitates efficient discovery and interaction between users and home service professionals.

The Allstate API offers access to insurance services, allowing users to manage claims and policies. Key features include endpoints for retrieving specific claims using a claim ID (/api/v1/claims/{claimId}), accessing policy information (/api/v1/policies), and listing claims (/api/v1/claims).

info.description: API for Adobe Photoshop cloud services and project management
info.title: Adobe Photoshop

summary: The Adobe Photoshop API provides cloud services and project management capabilities. It includes endpoints for managing projects, such as retrieving project details (/api/v1/projects), managing specific project layers (/api/v1/projects/{projectId}/layers), and monitoring storage usage (/api/v1/storage/usage). This API facilitates integration with Adobe Photoshop's cloud-based tools, enabling efficient project handling and resource management.
